Jean-Claude Trichet: Have sketched out in my Aachen speech some elements for consideration in the design of a longer-term vision for Europe.
The Single Market has not been at the centre of the EU political priorities for quite some time and should be re-launched
The Euro Plus Pact must be more than declarations. It must be followed up with concrete action.
We should prohibit individual countries from pursuing policies that can harm themselves and the euro area as a whole
The experience of the first twelve years of EMU suggests that the limits of de facto soft policy coordination have largely been exhausted
We assumed that countries had sufficient incentives to ‘keep their house in order’ and contribute to the common good of the euro area
A Europe that fully brings its economic and political weight to bear in an ever more globalised economy
An open and flexible Europe fostering education, entrepreneurship and innovation, with ample empl. opportunities and high standard of living
A Europe of stability and responsibility where the burdens of today’s adjustments are not shifted onto future generations
